Citation.sTitle: Transfer Enthalpies of Amino Acids and Glycine Peptides from Water to Aqueous Solutions of Trimethylamine N-oxide at 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Enthalpies of solution of glycine, L-alanine, L-serine, L-threonine, L-valine, diglycine and triglycine in aqueous solutions of trimethylamine N-oxide (TMAO) have been measured by calorimetry at 298.15 K. The results obtained were used to calculate the heterogeneous enthalpic interaction coefficients ( hAT ) between the amino acids or glycine peptides and the molecule of TMAO in water. These solution enthalpies have been used to calculate the transfer enthalpies () of the amino acids or glycine peptides from water to aqueous solutions of TMAO. It has been observed that the transfer enthalpies of the amino acids and glycine peptides from water to aqueous solutions of TMAO are monotonically positive over the investigated concentration ranges. The relative order of hAT and for amino acids are all L-serine greater than L-threonine greater than glycine greater than L-alanine greater than L-valine, whereas the sequence of glycine peptides is triglycine greater than diglycine greater than glycine. The results are discussed in terms of solute-solute and solute-solvent interactions.
Citation.sKeyword: Amino acid, Trimethylamine N-oxide, Glycine peptide, transfer enthalpy, heterogeneous
